[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927044&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927044&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


	There is no need for an MX record for CSNET -- all CSNET sites now
use domain names and their mail routes are advertised using MX RRs in the
domain system.  A few sites may still be sending out .CSNET return
addresses but those should go away shortly.

	At one point it was planned to have BITNET convert to domain names
as well (and as a result, a decision was made not to put .BITNET into
the domain tree).  I do not know the current status of their effort.

Craig

